# LLM self-debug (VibePrompter)

When changing chat, memory, tools, or providers — **run probes yourself** before asking the user to retest.

## Headless binaries (`src-tauri/`)

```powershell
cd E:\Software\OpenServer\domains\VibePrompter\src-tauri
cargo run --bin memory_probe          # memory eviction + recall (needs LM Studio on :1234)
cargo run --bin tool_call_probe       # parse + read_file execute (no LLM)
$env:TOOL_PROBE_LIVE='1'; cargo run --bin tool_call_probe  # full run_chat + folder scope
```

## Settings → Advanced → Agent scenario runner

- JSON scenarios via `chat_debug_run_scenario` — same pipeline as `chat_complete_stream`.
- Presets: `chatDebugMemoryScenarios.ts`, `chatDebugToolScenarios.ts`.
- Inspect `trace` (`status` phases: `tools`, `compressing_memory`), `result.text`, `result.sessionSummary`.

## Logs

`%AppData%\com.vibeprompter.app\logs\vibeprompter.log.*` — search `tool loop`, `tool follow-up`, `memory compression`.

## Tool-call regressions

1. `tool_call_probe` must parse Qwen `<|tool_call|>call:read_file{path:…}`.
2. Live probe: `trace_tools_phase: true`, `contains_tool_markup: false` in final text.
3. Workspace root must be set (Settings → Workspace) for `read_file` to succeed.

## Patch edits (research)

Today: model outputs full file in ` ```file path ` `` fences → `apply_workspace_write` replaces entire file.

Target: **surgical patches** — model emits changed hunks only; backend applies unified diff or search/replace blocks. See `workspace/fs.rs::write_file_checked`, `generatedFiles.ts`. Candidate formats: ` ```patch path` ` `, `apply_patch` tool, or line-range ` ```file path:12-40` ``.
